 Yes, the code is vulnerable. This function is susceptible to a buffer overflow (CWE-119) due to insufficient bounds checking when copying characters into the `param_buffer` array. The `param_len` variable keeps track of the current length of the string in the buffer, but there is no check to ensure it does not exceed the size of `param_buffer`. If an attacker can provide input that exceeds the 1024-byte limit, they can overflow the buffer, leading to arbitrary code execution (CVE-2019-11360).

To fix this vulnerability, you should add a check to ensure that `param_len` does not exceed the size of `param_buffer` before copying a character into the buffer. For example:

```c++
if (param_len < sizeof(param_buffer)) {
    param_buffer[param_len++] = *curchar;
} else {
    xtables_error(PARAMETER_PROBLEM,
                  "Parameter too long!");
}
```

This will prevent the buffer from being overflowed and mitigate the risk of arbitrary code execution.
